{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idf3cd8487-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s186"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"186"},"text":"§ 186.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Penalty","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Whoever, during the period or periods of time an invention has been ordered to be kept secret and the grant of a patent thereon withheld pursuant to section 181, shall, with knowledge of such order and without due authorization, willfully publish or disclose or authorize or cause to be published or disclosed the invention, or material information with respect thereto, or whoever willfully, in violation of the provisions of section 184, shall file or cause or authorize to be filed in any foreign country an application for patent or for the registration of a utility model, industrial design, or model in respect of any invention made in the United States, shall, upon conviction, be fined not more than $10,000 or imprisoned for not more than two years, or both.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idf3cd8488-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1952-07-19/ch950"},"text":"July 19, 1952, ch. 950","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/66/807"},"text":"66 Stat. 807","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/418/tIX/s9101/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–418, title IX, § 9101(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-08-23"},"text":"Aug. 23, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/1568"},"text":"102 Stat. 1568","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s20/j"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29, § 20(j)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-09-16"},"text":"Sept. 16, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/125/335"},"text":"125 Stat. 335","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idf3cd8489-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idf3cd848a-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on Title 35, U.S.C., 1946 ed., § 156 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1952-02-01/ch4/s6"},"text":"Feb. 1, 1952, ch. 4, § 6","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/66/5"},"text":"66 Stat. 5","children":[],"tail":", 6)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Language is changed.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idf3cd848b-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idf3cd848c-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2011—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29","children":[],"tail":" struck out “of this title” after “181” and after “184”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/418"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–418","children":[],"tail":", which directed the insertion of “willfully” after second reference to “whoever”, was executed by making the insertion after “or whoever”, as the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idf3cd848d-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idf3cd848e-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2011 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29","children":[],"tail":" effective upon the expiration of the 1-year period beginning on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-09-16"},"text":"Sept. 16, 2011","children":[],"tail":", and applicable to proceedings commenced on or after that effective date, see section 20("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":") of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t35/s2"},"text":"section 2 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idf3cd848f-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1988 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/418"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–418","children":[],"tail":" applicable, subject to certain qualifications and exceptions, to all United States patents, and to all licenses under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t35/s184"},"text":"section 184 of this title","children":[],"tail":", regardless of the date such patents or licenses are granted, and to all applications for such patents pending on or filed after "},{"tag":"date","attrib"